{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"title":"overlayBounds","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"overlayBounds","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBounds":{"title":"MLNCoordinateBounds","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncoordinatebounds","role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","fragments":[{"text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A rectangular area as measured on a two-dimensional map projection.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"title":"MLNOverlay","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","fragments":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","role":"collection","title":"MapLibre","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"}}}